summary: I was getting ready to play, and I was doing meet and greets, and I was getting ready, I was getting dressed, and I kept hearing...
text: I was getting ready to play, and I was doing meet and greets, and I was getting ready, I was getting dressed, and I kept hearing how loudly you were screaming for Charli XCX and Camila Cabello. And I was just thinking…I was thinking…Not trying to be presumptuous, but they’re gonna be great. They’re gonna be great! I’ve been putting out albums since I was sixteen, and it had a pretty predictable schedule. Over and over again, it was kind of the same pattern. Like, I’d make an album, I would put out the album, and then I’d go on tour. Make an album, put out the album and then I’d go on tour. And that happened five albums in a row. And then before I made this album I decided to do something different. I decided to take some time to figure out what my life would be like and what decisions I would make if I didn’t have a spotlight on me, and it was really, really, really important for me to do that. I spent a lot of time in the U.K. I really love the U.K. And what was so amazing about the whole thing… being gone from you and not being on tour, the most amazing thing happened. You understood why I had to take some time and what’s even better, you were here when I came back. So thank you so much. I missed you so much. I missed the feeling of standing here and being able to see all the way to the top row. By the way, hi guys! How’s everyone doing up top? I missed being able to look out and feel that connection with you guys when we’re all singing the same words, because I think one thing that possibly all of us have in common in this sold out stadium is we all like the feeling of connecting with someone else, whether that’s making a friend, telling someone you have a crush on them, and them saying that they have a crush on you too, or just having someone say “Oh my God I’ve been there. I’ve experienced what you’ve been through too. That’s not just you.” And so you guys give me that feeling every single time you show up and every single time you care about songs I write about my feelings. And I wanna say thank you for that because when feelings are involved, which they usually are, all that stuff is very, very, very delicate. You know what I mean?
source: Taylor’s speech before Delicate in Manchester, England (June 8th, 2018)

summary: So last tour me and my sister @babywerehopelessromantics made some tops we were really proud of. The Red tour we made tops and...
caption:
So last tour me and my sister @babywerehopelessromantics made some tops we were really proud of. The Red tour we made tops and signs we loved. This tour we went all out. Scrap the Sharpies, we got fabric paint and new ideas…..but we also got an extra helper…. Introducing our mum! Fan since the beginning but never came to a concert with us in case she “embarrassed us” despite our arguing (I think me and my sister can embarrass ourselves on our own with the screaming and the crying at each concert!). We loved every step of making these tops and cannot wait to wear them at Wembley on both nights! After coming home from work every night and spending hours up to our necks in paint they are finally done, and I have loved every minute of making them with @babywerehopelessromantics ❤️

If anyone is going to Wembley we will see you there! Our seat numbers are Friday 22nd - Block A6, Row F, Seats 1-3 Saturday 23rd - Section 142, Row 11, Seats 253 and 254 ❤️🐍❤️

summary: - I first became a fan when I saw someone post a couple of lyrics from We Are Never Getting Back Together on Twitter the day it...
body:
Things I wish I’d told Taylor

- I first became a fan when I saw someone post a couple of lyrics from We Are Never Getting Back Together on Twitter the day it was released.

The lyrics were: “You’d hide away and find your peace of mind with some indie record that’s much cooler than mine.”

I read them and that was it for me. I was like, this girl is CLEARLY a genius and can see into the nooks and crannies of the soul and make beautiful art from it.

I’d grown up dating indie boys (and I was kind of an indie girl myself) but I was so sick of how moody and serious and precious and male the whole scene was. I’d also just gone through a breakup, which wasn’t so bad, but had been left a bit open-ended and I was so over the whole thing.

I immediately went and listened to the song and it was just the perfect anthem to my life right at that moment in time.

I spent the next year probably exclusively listening to your back catalogue (and tbh I mostly still do). I am still sad that it took me until Red came out to listen to your music. Think of all those wasted years beforehand that I spent listening to boring indie bands I didn’t even like that much!

- I was so worried about you last year when you were gone. I worried about you every day, not knowing where in the world you were and whether you were okay with the trial pending and everything else going on.

IMAGINE my surprise when I discovered not only that you were happy and putting together the most amazing music of your career, but that you’d been staying just down the road from me the whole time. Did we see each other in the pub? Walk past each other in the park? Who knows! My mind was blown.

- I didn’t want to ask you too many questions in case they seemed intrusive and it felt like I was trying to interview you, but I had so many questions!

- I was also the victim of a grabby hand-up-the-skirt assault. Mine was in a massive crowd late at night somewhere with no CCTV and the guy slithered off into the heaving mass of people so quickly that I barely got a look at him. I didn’t report it at the time because I knew there was no way anything would come of it.

Now I know better — I know that even if I was just a statistic to the police, speaking up can make sure that this problem, which is so crazily widespread, is better documented and therefore more visible. Trying to get the world to take this issue seriously is so difficult, but if we stand up and are counted now then maybe we’ll make life a little easier for the women who come after us. By putting yourself through that trial and pursuing justice, you took a bullet for womankind and I’m sure people for generations to come will thank you for that. Thank you from me. I’m glad you were heard and I’m glad you got the justice you deserved. I hope you feel safe now.

- I put this down to a combination of the passage of time and your musical influence on my life, but I just don’t care what people think of me anymore! And it’s so freeing! We are pretty much the same age and I feel like you’re right there with me in that place. It’s great, isn’t it? I feel like I’ve carried around this big weight for years and now that I’ve cast it off I wish I’d been able to do it sooner. But then I think you just have to go through that for a bit. Growing up, eh? Who would choose it. From what my older friends tell me, it just continues to get better from this point on. That makes me so excited for us both.

-Just before you came on last night I felt a few drops of rain, even though the sky above was blue with just a few pathetic, puffy clouds. I overheard you say you wanted a rain show in the U.K. and I felt like the sky was trying so hard to rain for you. It couldn’t manage it in the end last night, but we’ve had words and it will try harder tonight and during the next few shows.

- Your everyday acts of kindness have a ripple effect and over the past few weeks and months I feel like I’ve been bobbing gently over each and every little wave until I eventually floated right up to you. I love that as well as your music and your career as an artist that your generosity and graciousness will be your legacy. It was an honour for me to be one of the people to document it and to make sure everyone in the world knows you as we know you. Keep changing and keep growing, but never stop being you. We’ll be with you every step of the way 💕

@taylorswift

It couldn’t manage it in the end last night, but we’ve had words and it will try harder tonight and during the next few shows.

- Your everyday acts of kindness have a ripple effect and over the past few weeks and months I feel like I’ve been bobbing gently over each and every little wave until I eventually floated right up to you. I love that as well as your music and your career as an artist that your generosity and graciousness will be your legacy. It was an honour for me to be one of the people to document it and to make sure everyone in the world knows you as we know you. Keep changing and keep growing, but never stop being you. We’ll be with you every step of the way 💕

@taylorswift
trail.content:
Things I wish I’d told Taylor

- I first became a fan when I saw someone post a couple of lyrics from We Are Never Getting Back Together on Twitter the day it was released.

The lyrics were: “You’d hide away and find your peace of mind with some indie record that’s much cooler than mine.”

I read them and that was it for me. I was like, this girl is CLEARLY a genius and can see into the nooks and crannies of the soul and make beautiful art from it.

I’d grown up dating indie boys (and I was kind of an indie girl myself) but I was so sick of how moody and serious and precious and male the whole scene was. I’d also just gone through a breakup, which wasn’t so bad, but had been left a bit open-ended and I was so over the whole thing.

I immediately went and listened to the song and it was just the perfect anthem to my life right at that moment in time.

I spent the next year probably exclusively listening to your back catalogue (and tbh I mostly still do). I am still sad that it took me until Red came out to listen to your music. Think of all those wasted years beforehand that I spent listening to boring indie bands I didn’t even like that much!

- I was so worried about you last year when you were gone. I worried about you every day, not knowing where in the world you were and whether you were okay with the trial pending and everything else going on.

IMAGINE my surprise when I discovered not only that you were happy and putting together the most amazing music of your career, but that you’d been staying just down the road from me the whole time. Did we see each other in the pub? Walk past each other in the park? Who knows! My mind was blown.

- I didn’t want to ask you too many questions in case they seemed intrusive and it felt like I was trying to interview you, but I had so many questions!

- I was also the victim of a grabby hand-up-the-skirt assault. Mine was in a massive crowd late at night somewhere with no CCTV and the guy slithered off into the heaving mass of people so quickly that I barely got a look at him. I didn’t report it at the time because I knew there was no way anything would come of it.

Now I know better — I know that even if I was just a statistic to the police, speaking up can make sure that this problem, which is so crazily widespread, is better documented and therefore more visible. Trying to get the world to take this issue seriously is so difficult, but if we stand up and are counted now then maybe we’ll make life a little easier for the women who come after us. By putting yourself through that trial and pursuing justice, you took a bullet for womankind and I’m sure people for generations to come will thank you for that. Thank you from me. I’m glad you were heard and I’m glad you got the justice you deserved. I hope you feel safe now.

- I put this down to a combination of the passage of time and your musical influence on my life, but I just don’t care what people think of me anymore! And it’s so freeing! We are pretty much the same age and I feel like you’re right there with me in that place. It’s great, isn’t it? I feel like I’ve carried around this big weight for years and now that I’ve cast it off I wish I’d been able to do it sooner. But then I think you just have to go through that for a bit. Growing up, eh? Who would choose it. From what my older friends tell me, it just continues to get better from this point on. That makes me so excited for us both.

-Just before you came on last night I felt a few drops of rain, even though the sky above was blue with just a few pathetic, puffy clouds. I overheard you say you wanted a rain show in the U.K. and I felt like the sky was trying so hard to rain for you. It couldn’t manage it in the end last night, but we’ve had words and it will try harder tonight and during the next few shows.

- Your everyday acts of kindness have a ripple effect and over the past few weeks and months I feel like I’ve been bobbing gently over each and every little wave until I eventually floated right up to you. I love that as well as your music and your career as an artist that your generosity and graciousness will be your legacy. It was an honour for me to be one of the people to document it and to make sure everyone in the world knows you as we know you. Keep changing and keep growing, but never stop being you. We’ll be with you every step of the way 💕

@taylorswift
